[2
Date: 5 Jul 2000 13:33:28 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Africa News Service, 5 Jul 2000 10:56 AM EST [edited

Campaign Against Lassa Fever Gathers Momentum
---------------------------------------------
FREETOWN: (Concord Times, 5 Jul 2000) - Health Education boss Mr. Valentine
has said that a campaign against Lass fever has started in Freetown.
Describing the outbreak as "very serious and a concern," Mr. Kawa said that
so far 4 people have died from the disease, which is occurring in Freetown
for the very first time. The 4 include a physician who died on 30 Jun 2000
and was buried without ceremonies and 3 other family members. A seminar on
Lassa Fever which was scheduled to take place early this week has been
postponed till further notice. The Health Education boss said that people
should improve their daily personal hygiene, report very high fever at
once, kill all rats by probably introducing a cat in the house and should
cover all foods and water.
"Tracing of close contacts with the deceased, Dr. Kabbah and his relatives
is also continuing and community Health Education has started on radio and
television," Mr. Kawa said.
[Byline: Sulaiman Momodu
--
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
[The gist of these 2 reports is that there have been "at least" 4 deaths in
Freetown, Sierra Leone, attributed to Lassa Fever. There may have been more
deaths. Two cases were reported in a July 1 news report in addition to the
4 cases reported here. It is not clear whether the diagnosis of Lassa fever
has been confirmed - Mod. CP
